This work demonstrates the integration of:
  - CyberArk Secure Workload Access (SWA) — vendor bundle, not redistributed.
  - CyberArk Secrets Manager – SaaS (Conjur Cloud) — public REST API.
  - Palo Alto Networks Idira brand identity — used per PANW brand guidelines.
  - SPIFFE / SPIRE — workload identity standard via github.com/spiffe/go-spiffe.

Third-party components used (each under its own license):
  - kind (Apache 2.0)
  - Helm (Apache 2.0)
  - Terraform (BSL 1.1) and providers cyberark/swa, cyberark/conjur (Apache 2.0)
  - Go and the Go standard library (BSD)
  - github.com/spiffe/go-spiffe/v2 (Apache 2.0)
  - Playwright (Apache 2.0)
  - distroless base images by Google (Apache 2.0)
  - Conceal + Summon (Apache 2.0) by CyberArk
